    approach: "- Start at the root and process level by level using the already-wired `next` pointers as a linked list for each level.\n- For each node `cur` on the current level, wire `cur->left->next = cur->right` (same parent cross) and `cur->right->next = cur->next->left` (cross-parent cross, when a right neighbor exists).\n- Descend to the leftmost child of the current level to begin the next level pass.\n- Because the tree is **perfect**, every internal node always has both children, so no null-child guards are needed beyond checking when we've exhausted a level. This runs in O(n) time with O(1) extra space (no queue).",
    code: "#include <cstddef>\nusing namespace std;\n\n// Node definition provided by the judge; reproduced here for compilation.\nclass Node {\npublic:\n    int val;\n    Node* left;\n    Node* right;\n    Node* next;\n    Node() : val(0), left(nullptr), right(nullptr), next(nullptr) {}\n    Node(int _val) : val(_val), left(nullptr), right(nullptr), next(nullptr) {}\n    Node(int _val, Node* _left, Node* _right, Node* _next)\n        : val(_val), left(_left), right(_right), next(_next) {}\n};\n\nclass Solution {\npublic:\n    Node* connect(Node* root) {\n        if (!root) return root;\n\n        // `levelStart` is the leftmost node of the level we are currently wiring.\n        Node* levelStart = root;\n\n        while (levelStart->left) {           // stop when we reach a leaf level\n            // Walk every node on this level using its next pointers.\n            for (Node* cur = levelStart; cur; cur = cur->next) {\n                // Connect left child to right child (same parent).\n                cur->left->next = cur->right;\n\n                // Connect right child to the left child of the next parent,\n                // if a right neighbour exists on this level.\n                if (cur->next)\n                    cur->right->next = cur->next->left;\n            }\n            // Drop down to the leftmost node of the next level.\n            levelStart = levelStart->left;\n        }\n\n        return root;\n    }\n};\n",
