    approach: "- Store each point's frequency in a 2-D count grid (heap-allocated 1001×1001) and maintain a map from x-coordinate to the set of distinct y-values seen at that x.\n- For a query point `(qx, qy)`, iterate over every distinct y-value `y2` recorded at the same x-column. The vertical edge `(qx,qy)-(qx,y2)` defines the side length `d = |y2-qy|`.\n- A valid axis-aligned square needs two more corners at `(qx±d, qy)` and `(qx±d, y2)`; multiply their counts together and accumulate. Multiplying frequencies correctly counts every combination of duplicate points.\n- `add` is O(1) amortised; `count` is O(N) where N is the number of distinct y-values stored in the query's x-column.",
    code: "#include <vector>\n#include <unordered_map>\n#include <unordered_set>\n#include <cstdlib>\nusing namespace std;\n\nclass DetectSquares {\n    // freq[x][y] = how many times (x,y) has been added\n    vector<vector<int>> freq;\n    // ys_at[x] = distinct y-values seen at column x\n    unordered_map<int, unordered_set<int>> ys_at;\n\npublic:\n    DetectSquares() : freq(1001, vector<int>(1001, 0)) {}\n\n    void add(vector<int> point) {\n        int x = point[0], y = point[1];\n        freq[x][y]++;\n        ys_at[x].insert(y);   // set ignores duplicates automatically\n    }\n\n    int count(vector<int> point) {\n        int qx = point[0], qy = point[1];\n        int result = 0;\n\n        // No points share the query's x-column -> no squares possible\n        if (!ys_at.count(qx)) return 0;\n\n        // Fix the second point on the same vertical line as the query\n        for (int y2 : ys_at[qx]) {\n            if (y2 == qy) continue;          // must form a non-degenerate edge\n            int d = abs(y2 - qy);            // side length\n\n            // Try both horizontal directions for the other two corners\n            for (int dx : {-d, d}) {\n                int nx = qx + dx;\n                if (nx < 0 || nx > 1000) continue;\n                // Multiply counts: each combination is one valid square\n                result += freq[qx][y2] * freq[nx][qy] * freq[nx][y2];\n            }\n        }\n        return result;\n    }\n};\n",
