    approach: "- Use bottom-up 1-D DP where `dp[i]` holds the minimum coins needed to form amount `i`.\n- Initialize `dp[0] = 0` (zero coins for zero amount) and every other entry to `amount + 1` as a sentinel for \"unreachable.\"\n- For each sub-amount from 1 to `amount`, try every coin: if the coin fits, update `dp[i] = min(dp[i], dp[i - coin] + 1)`.\n- After filling the table, any entry still exceeding `amount` is truly unreachable, so return -1 in that case.",
    code: "#include <vector>\n#include <algorithm>\nusing namespace std;\n\nclass Solution {\npublic:\n    int coinChange(vector<int>& coins, int amount) {\n        // dp[i] = fewest coins to reach exactly amount i\n        // sentinel: amount+1 is larger than any valid answer\n        vector<int> dp(amount + 1, amount + 1);\n        dp[0] = 0;  // base case: 0 coins needed for amount 0\n\n        for (int i = 1; i <= amount; ++i) {\n            for (int coin : coins) {\n                if (coin <= i) {\n                    dp[i] = min(dp[i], dp[i - coin] + 1);\n                }\n            }\n        }\n\n        // if dp[amount] is still the sentinel, the amount is unreachable\n        return dp[amount] > amount ? -1 : dp[amount];\n    }\n};\n",
